Package: monecascale
Title: Scalable Backends for MONECA Mobility Clustering
Description: Provides scalable clustering backends for the moneca package,
    including hierarchical degree-corrected stochastic block model
    (DC-SBM) inference via moneca_sbm(), bipartite / rectangular
    clustering via moneca_bipartite(), flow-based hierarchical clustering
    via the Map Equation and Infomap (moneca_flow()), and post-hoc
    hierarchy-level auto-selection via auto_segment_levels() (MDL elbow
    or mutual information plateau). Version 0.5.0 adds rr_from_duckdb()
    for out-of-core relative-risk computation pushed into DuckDB SQL,
    unblocking graphs that do not fit as dense matrices in R memory.
    Designed as a sibling package that extends moneca beyond
    classification-scale mobility matrices while reusing moneca's output
    contract and downstream analysis / plotting stack. The load-bearing
    theoretical observation is that moneca's relative-risk matrix RR = O / E
    is the DC-SBM residual under identity block interaction, so SBM
    inference is a principled scalable drop-in for the clique-enumeration
    step. For two-mode (rectangular) data, moneca_bipartite() extends this
    to the degree-corrected Latent Block Model (DcLbm) on scaled-rounded RR.
    Flow-based clustering offers an orthogonal perspective on hierarchical
    community detection.
Version: 0.5.0
